originalText.text: We chose Kip for our winter wedding, January 2016. He did a fantastic job of photographing our day for us. As a bride who planned her entire wedding, there was a fear with deciding who was going to be able to capture it best. We did not have a videographer at our wedding, so it was important to us to have someone who was going to be able to play our day out for us in photographs. Kip did just that. He guided us through the day, and took some breathtaking shots. His professionalism, creativity, and efficiency were some of the qualities that helped our day be the best day of our lives. We could not be happier with the work Kip did for us! We would highly recommend him to anyone looking for a photographer in the future; we hope to find an excuse to use his talents again in ours. Thanks Kip!

originalText.text: The photos are amazing, and he is easy to work with.  Kip is fun, creative and professional.  He is truly able to capture the magic of a moment.  There's a classic look to the photos, with a dash of retro, spunk, or modern funk --whatever is needed to allow his trained eye to make the most of the subjects and their moment.  I have worked with Kip in a large party atmosphere,  family photos, and head shots, and have always been blown away by the quality:   I recommend him time and time again.

originalText.text:
With all of the buzz and craziness of our wedding day, it was such a relief to have a photographer who didn't need endless direction or guidance.

Kip Carter did not miss a single moment, he captured perfectly the essence of the day. In addition to taking gorgeous photos, Kip helped to keep everyone in our wedding party happy and in the right place at the right time. He was essential to make our wedding day better than we could have ever hoped.

Thanks, Kip!

Nick and Emily Baldwin

originalText.text: Kip's work is absolutely amazing! He is so easy to work with and has extremely reasonable prices.  I would highly recommend him to anyone.  We've done two sessions so far (family photos and a 'cake smash') and I'm so incredibly happy with all our photos.  I look forward to working with Kip again in the near future.

originalText.text: Kip's a fun-loving guy with an excellent sense of aesthetics--the kind of qualities you want in a photographer.  We hired him for our wedding back in 2014 when he was just starting out, and he sure delivered.  I would definitely recommend him to anyone.
